headline: The S&P 500 Just Hit Correction Territory: Here Are 5 Stocks That Are Simply Too Cheap to Ignore Right Now
summary: On March 13, the S&P 500 finished the day down 10% from its previous all-time high.  This officially pushed the stock market into what's known as "correction" territory, even if this is a misnomer.  After all, who's to say whether the price of the S&P 500 is more correct today versus yesterday or tomorrow?
